b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48134.htm)  [Next](sbe48136.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n37\\. And on account of the procedure, on the ascertainment of the non-being of\nthat.\n\nThat a _S_ udra is not qualified for knowledge of Brahman appears from that\nfact also that as soon as Gautama has convinced himself that _G_ abala, who\nwishes to become his pupil, is not a _S_ udra, he proceeds to teach him the\nknowledge of Brahman.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 38. And on account of the prohibition of hearing, studying, and\nperformance of (Vedic) matter](sbe48136.htm)\n\n'